      "id": 1,
      "title": "Anomaly Detection Methodology",
      "type": "text",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 6,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0
      },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "# Anomaly Detection Center\n\nStatistical outlier and behavioral anomaly detection in three layers:\n\n- **Layer 1 (Univariate)**: Static percentile bounds; z-score vs rolling mean/std. Metrics: `behavior_index_static_*`, `behavior_index_zscore*`.\n- **Layer 2 (Dynamic)**: EWMA baseline and k*std bands; residual z-score. Metrics: `behavior_index_baseline`, `*_band`, `*_residual*`, `*_seasonal_anomaly`, `*_residual_anomaly`.\n- **Layer 3 (Multivariate)**: Mahalanobis-style (diagonal) distance across behavior index + subindices. Metrics: `hbc_multivariate_md_score`, `hbc_multivariate_md_anomaly`.\n\n**Thresholds:** Z-score anomaly |z| > 2.5; residual anomaly |z| > 2.5; MD anomaly score > 15.\n\n**Related:** [Behavior Index Global](http://localhost:3001/d/behavior-index-global) | [Regional Deep Dive](http://localhost:3001/d/regional-deep-dive) | [Risk Regimes](http://localhost:3001/d/risk-regimes). See `docs/HBC_ANOMALY_ARCHITECTURE.md` for formulas."
      }
    },
